Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.48,0:00:12.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There, it's dealt with.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.67,0:00:19.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what it is you hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.40,0:00:24.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't believe a word an Another says.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.25,0:00:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or anything you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.91,0:00:32.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But still, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.06,0:00:37.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You want to solve problems\N with the Anothers by talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.97,0:00:41.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.27,0:00:45.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You can deal with a case I'm working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.02,0:00:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have you solve\Nit with those Ears of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.60,0:00:55.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It involves something at the Olympic Stadium.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:29.50,Ep_Title,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,#10 "White Cocoons and Blue Flames"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.35,0:02:38.51,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.66,0:02:40.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Aida-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.80,0:02:43.39,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.32,0:02:48.45,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Ryo woke up, thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.96,0:02:50.27,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.87,0:02:52.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.53,0:02:55.24,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You kept your promise, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.24,0:02:57.91,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Ryo, you thank him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.92,0:03:03.91,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.40,0:03:19.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you solved Aida-san's problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:20.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Senda-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:23.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.85,0:03:25.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.66,0:03:31.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to talk, we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.15,0:03:33.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:37.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The elites at City Hall can be pretty brutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.85,0:03:41.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say for sure that\N Kanoichi-san is wrong, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.03,0:03:44.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can't accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.60,0:03:48.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, just stomping on him was brutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.59,0:03:53.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Same with viewing Anothers as just \Nthings to be killed or spared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.76,0:03:56.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Sakaki-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.18,0:03:59.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kanoichi Satoru's way of handling it aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.76,0:04:04.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,it was the best option in terms of making\N sure there were no more casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.05,0:04:06.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:09.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not saying the way you do things is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.85,0:04:15.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried when I saw you were\N sympathetic to Azazel, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.59,0:04:21.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Your Ears seem to make you\N way too sympathetic to Anothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.71,0:04:23.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When that works out, great.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.25,0:04:28.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But some day, it might not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.14,0:04:35.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to realize that the Ears of Sand\N aren't some kind of all-powerful skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.32,0:04:37.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They have their downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.78,0:04:41.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep that in mind when you use them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.48,0:04:44.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,we'll be there to be back you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.32,0:04:45.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.00,0:04:47.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Theo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.77,0:04:52.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a great team.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.75,0:04:54.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're very cute—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.63,0:04:57.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, very talented... workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.35,0:04:59.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,As your boss, I'm very proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.41,0:05:04.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The elites at City Hall, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.42,0:05:11.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,From what Miyako-kun said,\N something seems dangerous about that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.30,0:05:13.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.44,0:05:18.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever someone gets\N arrogant, they always fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:29.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The details are as I wrote in my email.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.32,0:05:32.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.13,0:05:37.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, there's an Another\N in the Stadium, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.64,0:05:40.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The construction work\N is falling behind, you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.81,0:05:43.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is that because of the Another?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.53,0:05:48.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's better to say it might fall behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.82,0:05:50.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.40,0:05:52.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You'll know when we get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.27,0:05:59.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're aware of why City Hall\N is getting involved, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.11,0:06:02.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's the main event area for the Olympics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.13,0:06:21.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is this all... Anothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.88,0:06:24.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.65,0:06:26.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's like the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:32.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There've been other small\N problems involving Anothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.60,0:06:34.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,but never of this scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:38.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Normal people can't see this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:40.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.63,0:06:45.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So they can come and \Ngo easily, and keep this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.36,0:06:48.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's causing lots of accidents,\N though. Obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.09,0:06:51.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We rushed here immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.97,0:06:54.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But it was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.15,0:06:57.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We realized the mistake we'd made...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.42,0:07:00.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't many Anothers\N in this area to serve as predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.46,0:07:03.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So it was the perfect place to lay eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.40,0:07:07.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We tried removing them little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.86,0:07:11.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But the next day we came back\N and there were more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.02,0:07:14.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We got nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.54,0:07:21.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But if you can use your Ears\N of Sand to talk to the Another,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.70,0:07:23.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,it would help us a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:26.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We'd save money on our budget, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.97,0:07:32.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What Anothers are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.41,0:07:35.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, is there anything even inside these?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.65,0:07:38.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We cracked one open to check.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.95,0:07:42.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It appeared to be some kind of insect Another.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.18,0:07:43.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Insect?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.73,0:07:45.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So these are cocoons?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.78,0:07:50.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Miyako-san, use your Ears of Sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.78,0:07:54.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Miyako-san!\NIt's dangerous to go alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.13,0:07:59.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What cocoons are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.71,0:08:00.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:04.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You don't hear any voices?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.67,0:08:06.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.67,0:08:09.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.73,0:08:14.16,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I hear something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.09,0:08:30.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.51,0:08:34.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's spitting something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.99,0:08:37.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's spinning a thread...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.88,0:08:47.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There're bigger problems here\N than not being able to talk to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.83,0:08:49.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Miyako-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.39,0:08:54.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear something?\NDid they say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.87,0:08:58.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The voice... of a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.03,0:09:00.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.49,0:09:02.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're just what they looked like, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.62,0:09:08.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What about the parent Another?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.48,0:09:13.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We thought of that,\Nbut we have yet to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.35,0:09:17.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So why don't you ask them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.03,0:09:20.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'd appreciate it, personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.94,0:09:24.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we know the cause, we can\N remove it at the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.32,0:09:27.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And then this will never happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.00,0:09:30.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.70,0:09:41.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You knew, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.09,0:09:43.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You knew from the start, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.45,0:09:45.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You made me do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.14,0:09:47.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, we have to eliminate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.93,0:09:53.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't do it, we'll have to burn them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.00,0:09:55.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.89,0:09:58.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Any other ideas, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.95,0:10:02.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to tell me we should\N just leave them here, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.43,0:10:06.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But after seeing them\N and hearing their voices...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.99,0:10:11.73,Flashback_Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Your ears seem to make you\N way too sympathetic to Anothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:17.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What is there to think about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.24,0:10:18.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.65,0:10:23.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're in humanity's territory.\N Some people have even gotten hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.20,0:10:26.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we want to get rid of them,\N we need to do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.59,0:10:33.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you know that and your\N Ears of Sand still can't help you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.94,0:10:35.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're just in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.40,0:10:41.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, we'll all begin to \Nhandle this with members of City Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:43.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and the ward offices as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.93,0:10:46.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But you're not required to attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.66,0:10:51.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shimizu-san, I'd like to explain what we're \Ndoing tomorrow. Please remain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.62,0:10:55.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako-san, tomorrow, please return\N to your regular office to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.85,0:10:58.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.29,0:11:53.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Feeling down, Arata?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:55.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kohaku...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.42,0:11:58.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.20,0:12:00.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What a sight it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.71,0:12:03.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's not something you see every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:05.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's something unique to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.97,0:12:07.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what those cocoons are?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.99,0:12:09.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're just what they look like.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.81,0:12:14.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen humans doing\N similar things, a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.49,0:12:18.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, the festival is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.68,0:12:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.30,0:12:22.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jealous, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.53,0:12:26.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I could make myself the perfect\N thing with that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.05,0:12:28.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll ask for some.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.05,0:12:31.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think so, Arata?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.65,0:12:35.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand your words, but still\N have no idea what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.01,0:12:36.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.89,0:12:39.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you when it's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.52,0:12:42.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Look forward to it!  Promise me you will!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.23,0:12:48.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,As always, I have no idea what that was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.67,0:12:55.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.95,0:12:57.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.65,0:13:05.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd he run off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.74,0:13:31.74,sign_6555_61_April_6th___Shin,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,City Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.20,0:13:33.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Akane-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.50,0:13:37.00,sign_6555_61_April_6th___Shin,,0000,0000,0000,,Imperial Gardens
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.50,0:13:37.00,sign_9692_112_Shinjuku_Imperia,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjuku Imperial Gardens
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.69,0:13:40.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Was I just being naïve?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.03,0:13:44.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this time it was a really bad matchup.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.03,0:13:47.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A humanoid bug-type that looks like a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:50.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.95,0:13:52.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What would you do, Kyoichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.99,0:13:58.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, the first thing\N I'd do is try to move the cocoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.03,0:14:03.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What Kanoichi Satoru said\N would be my last option.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.04,0:14:08.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I should've snuck in and gotten a sample!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.78,0:14:10.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you get one?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.57,0:14:13.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I didn't think of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.39,0:14:15.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That idiot Kanoichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.74,0:14:19.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If he chose to get rid of them, then\N he'd better have taken a sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.87,0:14:20.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Theo...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.04,0:14:24.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,From the perspective of a scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.86,0:14:27.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,getting rid of all the Anothers is a bad move.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.04,0:14:49.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you got in a fight with Miyako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.30,0:14:55.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shimizu-kun told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.54,0:14:58.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.17,0:15:02.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you take him off today's job?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.91,0:15:05.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Because we don't need him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.03,0:15:05.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.12,0:15:10.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Akane-san, you like\Nto take his side, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:18.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, I've started to understand\N how Suzu-sama feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.29,0:15:20.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Suzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.51,0:15:22.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The house god?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.03,0:15:27.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I don't know what she's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.23,0:15:29.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So I have to guess from\N her facial expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.61,0:15:32.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's just your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.01,0:15:34.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Communication with\N Anothers is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.26,0:15:39.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Since Miyako-san came, I feel like\N I'm a little closer to Suzu-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.37,0:15:41.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You can't trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.57,0:15:43.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He's close to the Anothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.80,0:15:44.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He's like...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.63,0:15:46.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.05,0:16:02.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When I see how Miyako-san\Ntreats the Anothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.96,0:16:07.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I remember my uncle... your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.64,0:16:10.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He was Suzu-sama's friend, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:17.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:22.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you keep it as a sign of your\N hatred toward the Kanoichi clan?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.60,0:16:30.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Anothers...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.93,0:16:36.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,drive men mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.27,0:16:42.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So we should get rid of them\N as soon as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.79,0:16:47.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But surely you understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.05,0:16:51.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,what those cocoons are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.13,0:16:54.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's no other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.87,0:17:05.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious about what Huehuecóyotl said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.51,0:17:08.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He said there'd be a "festival" soon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.23,0:17:10.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.28,0:17:13.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Which means... Izumo, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.15,0:17:15.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Izumo?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.01,0:17:17.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard of Kaminashizuki,\N the godless month, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.21,0:17:19.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,In Izumo, they call it Kamiarizuki,\N the month of gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.40,0:17:22.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um, in October of the old Japanese calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.90,0:17:26.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,all the gods of Japan gather\N in Izumo and have a festival, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.39,0:17:27.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.57,0:17:30.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,For that reason, in September\N of the old calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.72,0:17:34.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,the Anothers start to vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.29,0:17:40.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably getting ready to head\Nto Izumo, or getting ready for the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.42,0:17:44.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He said humans have been doing it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.59,0:17:46.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Insects and cocoons...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:49.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Silkworms?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.83,0:17:50.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.37,0:17:52.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably harvesting silk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.28,0:17:54.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.97,0:17:57.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Not good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.71,0:18:02.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If Huehuecóyotl was talking\N about the Izumo festival...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.64,0:18:05.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then the Anothers are using\N cocoons to make silk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.89,0:18:07.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.48,0:18:11.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kanoichi-san said he couldn't find\N the mother of the cocoon babies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.52,0:18:16.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But even Kanoichi Satoru's operating on\N the assumption that she exists at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.29,0:18:21.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He opted for burning them\N because of the location.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.70,0:18:26.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably getting pressure\Nfrom above to solve this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.88,0:18:31.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the mother does show up,\N he may assume he can deal with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.03,0:18:35.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they do, he'll be able to—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.54,0:18:39.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No! If we're right, this is seriously bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:40.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We can't burn them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.93,0:18:44.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If they're for a festival of the gods,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.42,0:18:47.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,they're not something humans should mess with!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.70,0:18:55.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll follow the plan we discussed yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.27,0:18:58.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Use the talismans I passed out to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.84,0:19:10.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, they generate purifying\N flames that only work on Anothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.52,0:19:12.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They don't work in a wide area,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.58,0:19:17.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,so you're unfortunately going\N to have to put one on each cocoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.31,0:19:20.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's get to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.96,0:19:38.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.73,0:19:41.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to make my clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.41,0:19:45.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What an awful thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:54.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I get rid of those humans for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.99,0:20:02.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Tch... I thought I could\Nget her to owe me one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.11,0:20:09.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we'll be done by morning at this rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.57,0:20:16.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we were able\N to deal with this quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.19,0:20:19.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's fast when you've got a team this size.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.96,0:20:23.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Once this is done, can you help\N with the stands, Yamaoka?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.38,0:20:26.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They seem to be running behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.53,0:20:32.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yamaoka?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.05,0:20:47.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! It showed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.46,0:20:48.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.34,0:21:26.34,sign_30794_260_Shimizu__Chiyoda,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shimizu \N{\fs16\b0}Chiyoda Ward Nocturnal Relations Division
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.19,0:21:26.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shimizu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.39,0:21:28.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.09,0:21:30.04,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.17,0:21:33.52,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What do we do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.52,0:21:35.22,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.22,0:21:36.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.58,0:21:39.68,Italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody's wrapped up in cocoons...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.93,0:21:46.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She got all of them b-but me!
